<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870707-0140 </DOCNO><HL> Sterling Drug Japanese Venture</HL><DD> 07/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STY </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sterling Drug Inc. said it plans to enter the Japanese household-products market with a joint venture to market Sterling's Lysol spray disinfectant.    Sterling's joint-venture partner is Kobayashi Pharmaceutical Co., of Japan, which makes drugs and household products. The two companies didn't release terms of their venture.    Sterling already sells prescription and over-the-counter medicines and consumer products in Japan. </TEXT></DOC>